{"key":"processedPost-5726486","value":{"id":5726486,"first":5726364,"last":5726713,"when":1149789420,"utime":"06/08/06 08:57 PM","content":"Don't use hay.  Hay is the end of the stalk with the seeds, and they will contaminate very easily, being grains.  Use straw, coffee grinds, coir, worm castings, compost, or a combination of any or all to cut the manure if you want.  Verm is ok to cut it, but bear in mind it won't supply any food value.<br />RR","title":"Re: No Straw for my HPoo; Hay, Nothing, Something Else?"}}